---
    import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
    ---

    <Layout title="Large Language Models">
      <main class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
        <section class="text-center mb-16">
          <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
            Large Language Models
          </h1>
          <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
            Explore the world of Large Language Models with our articles and tutorials.
          </p>
        </section>
        <section class="mt-10">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Notes</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700">
            <li>This page provides content related to Large Language Models.</li>
            <li>It includes articles and tutorials about LLM concepts and applications.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>
        <section class="mt-10">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
            Understanding Large Language Models
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-8">
            Large Language Models (LLMs) are a type of artificial intelligence that can understand and generate human-like text. Here are some key aspects:
          </p>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-12">
            <div class="p-6 border rounded-lg shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                Transformer Architecture
              </h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600">
                LLMs are typically based on the transformer architecture, which allows for parallel processing of text.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="p-6 border rounded-lg shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                Pre-training and Fine-tuning
              </h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600">
                LLMs are pre-trained on massive datasets and then fine-tuned for specific tasks.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="p-6 border rounded-lg shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                Few-Shot Learning
              </h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600">
                LLMs can perform tasks with only a few examples, making them highly adaptable.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="p-6 border rounded-lg shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                Text Generation
              </h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600">
                LLMs can generate coherent and contextually relevant text, making them useful for content creation.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="p-6 border rounded-lg shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                Language Understanding
              </h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600">
                LLMs can understand the nuances of human language, including context and intent.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="p-6 border rounded-lg shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                Applications
              </h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600">
                LLMs are used in various applications, including chatbots, language translation, and content generation.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            LLMs are a rapidly evolving field with immense potential to transform how we interact with technology.
          </p>
        </section>
        <section class="mt-10">
          <article class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
            <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
              <div class="flex-1">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
                  <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-gray-100 text-gray-700 rounded-full text-sm">RAG</span>
                  <span class="text-gray-500">Jan 5, 2024</span>
                  <span class="mx-2">•</span>
                  <span class="text-gray-500">26 min read</span>
                </div>
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">
                  <a href="/blog/rag-systems" class="hover:text-primary">
                    A Crash Course on Building RAG Systems – Part 9 (With Implementation)
                  </a>
                </h2>
                <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
                  A deep dive into ColPali for building vision-driven RAG systems (with implementation).
                </p>
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                  <div class="flex -space-x-2">
                    <img src="https://api.dicebear.com/7.x/avataaars/svg?seed=Avi" alt="Avi Chawla" class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full border-2 border-white" />
                    <img src="https://api.dicebear.com/7.x/avataaars/svg?seed=Akshay" alt="Akshay Pachaar" class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full border-2 border-white" />
                  </div>
                  <span class="text-gray-700">Avi Chawla, Akshay Pachaar</span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <img src="https://placehold.co/200x150" alt="Article thumbnail" class="w-48 h-36 object-cover rounded-lg" />
            </div>
          </article>
        </section>
        <section class="mt-10 text-center">
          <a href="https://www.google.co.in/books/edition/LLM_Engineer_s_Handbook/jHEqEQAAQBAJ?hl=en&gbpv=1&dq=llm%20link&pg=PA49&printsec=frontcover" class="text-primary hover:underline">
            Learn more in the LLM Engineer's Handbook
          </a>
        </section>
      </main>
    </Layout>
